76561197979223944,Recommended,266510,32892545,Posted: 27 June,all,Binks,"It's honestly a bit hard to explain this game, since it's such a mash of game elements. The general gameplay of moving from point to point and dealing with the events there feels very FTL, but then the combat kicks in and it's assassin's creed/arkham style fighting with counters, and the overarching deckbuilding mechanics are a whole layer of their own. The game is immensely fun, the enemy you face is full of character (with just a few random lines and some scripting they've achieved a character more interesting than most triple-A titles churn out these days...), and unlike most rogue-likes, you can make ongoing long-term progress even if you fail your main quest, in the form of unlocking new cards to encounter or use on your quest.Honestly if you like rogue-like games at all I would check this one out, as it's overflowing with character. If you happen to be like me, and enjoy rogue-likes, counterattack combat, and deckbuilding, what are you waiting for?"
