,Recommended,266510,14521988,"Posted: 17 February, 2015",all,Trevellian[C22],"I have only played Hand of Fate for through about half of the Story mode decks but, I must say it is one of the greatest games I have ever played.Combining the death and start over mechanic of a Rogue Like, with the addictive nature of a Deck Builder was an absolutely brilliant idea.  Having the encounters with monster cards be played out in a slightly Arkham Style (Attack/Counter/Dodge/Stun) was an even further brilliant idea.  Although the combat is the weakest part with a fixed camera, it is still manageable and fun.  Trap Rooms are also played out in this 3rd person camera style as you dodge your way through a trap maze.Even if you complete all 12 of the storymode levels there is an Endless mode to see how far you can go.  The game starts out relatively simple, but starts to become challenging about 1/4 of the way through the Story decks.Add to this the amazing way it's presented, the dealer is well voice acted and doesn't get annoying.I cannot recommend this game enough.It's reminds me of playing a game of Munchkin, but against a dealer instead of a group of friends.  Absolutely brilliant."
