,Recommended,266510,26170785,"Posted: 22 October, 2016",all,Sydney's World,"Halfway through the game I can recommend (when on sale) to those interested in a combination strategy/rouge experience. The strategy part isn't that deep however; mostly you have to decide how to keep enough food and health (and get some good gear) to reach the boss. Beat the boss, and start fresh on each new level. Though there isn't that much variety in turns of battling (bascially move really fast/dodge/attack, repeat), there is enough skill challenge to keep it fairly interesting. Hand of Fate is more than the sum of its parts: everything comes together to give you 12 short and relatively enjoyable rouge-like levels in story mode. Chance has more of an effect in your ability to beat a level than most games, and sometimes luck will go against you. Only had really bad luck in one level out of 6 so far, which perhaps means the odds are stacked in the player's favor. Three consecutive pain cards was indeed painful; lost 60 health right before boss, lost boss battle, needed to repeat entire level.     7/10: Would randomnly lose 60 health again."
