,Recommended,266510,24729313,"Posted: 5 August, 2016",all,Click,"Need to change my review a little bit since I finally beat it the game on default difficulty.The difference between the early game and the late game is night and day. Early game is fun and exciting, the late game is nearly the opposite.Only play this game if you are OK with random events being the reason you lose. You can be very good at combat (telegraphed enemy attacks help) and understand the cards and what to choose (when you have real choice) but still die to 25% chances of bad things happen or getting a bad curse.The combat is basic, the concept is fantastic, and the game is technically very replayable across it's characters and game types as long as you are able to tolerate the punishing randomness.  I hope Hand of Fate 2 has ironed out some of the problem that this game has with it's late game. I do like the game and will therefore recommend it but not to anyone."
