76561198013195134,Recommended,266510,16512137,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,Dr. Spankenstein,"I've only played a bit so far, but before the sale is over I wanted to get this out.  It's really a neat idea for a game, and I'm having a blast with it.It's basically a procedurally generated game, but procedural generation is affected by a deck you put together and the AI puts together.  It plays out like a board game, where each card is a space you can move to.  Each game has several of these cars laid out.  Somewhere towards the end of this trail of cards is a boss to slay.  Each time you move. the card you land on is revealed.  You may have a choice to make, an oppurtunity to shop with gold, or end up fighting.  Combat will cause the cards to create a small arena and an opponent or opponents for you to fight.  Combat is simplistic, attack, stun, counter, or dodge.  It works though, and the enemies look cool.  Love the slow-mo effect on the finishing blow to the last enemy.  Speaking of face-crunching weapons, those come from cards as well, as do food and gold.  These are drawn whenever you receive items from a encounter card, or on display at the various shop cards.  Food is expended when you move your piece.The narrator you play with has a lot of character, as someone else has pointed out.  I was genuinely enjoying listening to his commentary on my choices and the cards on the table.  His presence really makes you feel like you sat down to play a game with him.  Occasionally he'll tempt you into undertaking a card's challenge by offering you a token that will unlock other cards for your deck.  I can see this getting me killed eventually, but they are so shiny...The variety in the cards from the get go is interesting.  Without spoiling anything (half the fun is in the suprise I think), I was suprised my many of the encounters.  They can be very creative, especially the ones that require decisions.I've killed two bosses thus far, and if I didn't have real life stuff to do I'd be up for a while with this.Long story short, the atmosphere and suprise in the game are amazing.  It's like sitting down and playing a board or card game, but being teleported into a fantasy location for combat.  It is absolutely worth the sale price if you think you would enjoy playing a mysterious game of cards with a good beat down session every thirty seconds or so."
