76561198029300088,Recommended,266510,26738992,"Posted: 21 November, 2016",all,yenkin2001,"The First time I saw this game in my queue; I watched the video and said no thanks.  Few months later I am looking for a game to play while searching Google for ARPG style games and this game was on the list.  Went back and re-looked at the game a second time.  The reviews are good, with what I would say is a 90% rating based on the number of positive to negative reviews.  Sometimes my gut is wrong, after reading recent reviews trolling the discussion I decided for the 30$ CAD it might be worth a look see.There is a lot of goodness going on in this game; it pits you as the player against a dungeon master like character.  There is a randomness to the game that is fresh as you use decks of cards to determine how the game progresses.  This is an interesting concept, but there is a twist even through you can control the encounter deck, don’t expect the dealer to play fair especially as the game progresses.The cards are dealt you move your table top piece unto the next encounter card, it plays out like a choose your own adventure novel, where you can encounter helpful goblins, or find yourself at the mercy of angry mobs.  There is also an arena type encounter where you fight in almost an arcade style fighting, cards determine how many mobs and of what type.  All leading to a Boss card at the end, the pace in the arcade game is pretty quick, but manageable even for old coots like myself.IF anything, the game suffers a bit from a lack of a good tutorial, there is a small game to begin your series, but it lacks instructions, while it is not hard, it would be nice to understand the mechanics a bit more before you are thrown into the fray.  The arcade sequence is a bit twitch as you have to use wasd as movement, along with Q and the 1 and 2 buttons, as well as the spacebar.  I am more comfortable now, but there can be a lot going on when you are being attacked by a large group when you are trying to figure out the combat mechanics.There is no game save feature, you play, leave and resume.  Not sure if you can start over even if you wanted too. It also offers no player avatar customization, so you can’t choose what your avatar looks like, pity I think that is important sometimes to create that affinity between the player and the game.Overall 7.5/10, this is a good solid fun casual game that is unique to play.  It offers up a never ending play value as you never know what the cards will have in store for you.  I think a few tweaks and this game easily could be 10.  Buy it and support them in the Sequel HOF2."
