76561197993294002,Recommended,266510,14670094,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,Daklor,"This is the first Steam review I have ever written, I normally wouldn't write them, but I enjoy this game so very much that I thought I would share my thoughts.This game is, hands down, one of the most compelling roguelike-rpg-combat games I have ever played. It has a very tight core gameplay loop, it scratches that collectable itch, and the combat is fun, with enough mechanics to keep it interesting.But let me speak to the one feature that really sold this game to me. The Dealer. God I hate that man. But I also love him. He narrates the game, he goads you, he encourages you, he hints at a story behind why you and him are playing the game, Every snide aside and every grudging compliment I feel like I earn, and when I defeat one of his cards I literally whoop with victory.As for the RNG (random number generator for those not familar with acronyms) aspect of the game, I never feel like it was unfair, because you can choose which cards to include in your deck. For the past 3 games I was insta killed by one particular card. Am I complaining? No, I chose to include that card specifically because I want to unlock the next card after that. I like to intentionally make the hardest deck I can, just to see if I can beat it. Because there is that element of choice, I never feel like the game is unfair.Finally, the difficulty curve. It is rather seductive. It lures you in the first couple of bosses, and then decides to smack you around a bit. I like it, I feel like it lengthens the game. The one issue I have is that I feel like it was way too easy on the outset, so I managed to get to the 10th boss with minimal losses. That could be just me, and it is taking quite a few runs to even see the boss I am currently on.That gets to my final point, and only criticism, such as it is. I need more. I am worried I will be running out of cards to find, of things to see, and I need more. Fortunately the game seems very well set up to add content to, and I for one will be getting whatever the developers put out. I hope they support this game for a very long time.I wholeheartly recommend this game to players who enjoy a good dungeon crawl, who like paying for their mistakes, and especially to those who love the feel of a board game, where you can look across the table at your opponent and think, ""Time to take this jacka-- down. """
