76561198102773181,Recommended,266510,31903185,Posted: 22 May,all,Bluejoy,"This game is amazing. Part Action RPG, part Rogue-like, the game scratches so many itches. Basically, it plays like this - you walk through a series of randomized encounters in a top-down board game. Most of these encounters take you to an action-rpg combat scene, where you fight randomized batches of enemies. When you get to the end of a scenario, you fight a boss, and the deck gets reshuffled for the next one. However, for each encounter you complete, you unlock new possible encounters, and before each scenario, you get to choose which encounters you want to have in the deck. This gives the player massive control over difficulty and playstyle, while also adding strategy elements to your preparation before each scenario. Trying to unlock new cards becomes an exploration goal, while completing scenarios and beating bosses is a skill-based challenge, especially considering the combat system, which revolves around well times dodges and counterattacks. The randomized elements make each playthrough unique, increasing replayability and allowing for the thrill of both very lucky finds and very unlucky match-ups.This game is extremely well balaned. If you lack the skill to overcome one challenge, the game provides others to keep you invested. Without realizing it, you keep playing until you realize you've gotten better, or that you've gotten some helpful cards, and maybe now you can beat that boss after all. There's quite a lot of content in the main game, and it comes at an even and rewarding pace.Also, the art and graphics are beautiful, the music is good, the voice acting is charming and the overall game feel is incredible. The game sucks you in and makes you want to unlock more, do more, get better, but because individual sessions are not too long and, in a pinch, the game can save midsession, there are lots of exit points if you're not able to play for hours on end.Worth every penny."
