,Recommended,266510,32263419,Posted: 8 June,all,Angry Toast,"Absolutely excellent game! I only have a couple hours on it, but from playing it I love how the game handles.You play through a deck of cards magically generated with cards you collect and cards the dealer holds. Each card has either a good or bad effect on you, and you explore these slowly elaborately growing dungeons to find the exit. You can go from talking to a merchant and equipping gear you own to fighting an army of bandits. The combat is very fluid, tight and easy to pick up. You are slowly put into the ringer and shown everything you need to know before the real challenges come out. Trust me, the difficulty picks up fast, but at least you can better equip yourself as you progress, because you unlock more useful encounters/equipment cards from beating the dealer at his own game. Its highly addicting and superbly fun! Give it a go, its worth every penny and even buy the DLC its excellent too!"
