,Recommended,266510,11245445,"Posted: 15 July, 2014",all,DrTeaSpoon,"Brilliant Concept!Interesting combination of:-Choose your own adventure (Like those books) :: Every card in your encounter deck is like single page in that kind of book. You build your own deck from the cards you have unlocked.-Action Adventure Game (god of war) :: While the combat is not impressive looking and visceral as those games tend to be, the combat has strategic and dynamic elements to keep you on your toes.-Rogue Like :: Rogue likes have always been about exploration and resource management. This game offers that in spades.When I played this for first few runs, I thought that ""Soon I've seen all the encounters and items so it will lose it's charm"" but I discovered that some of the encounter cards are not set in stone. They have multiple ""forms"". For example encounter called ""Rock Fall"" had very different conclusion.Also when player is given ""random"" positive or negative conclusion to encounter the player draws from Four different cards.Cards can be any combination of Fail, Greater Fail, Success, Greater Success.The fact that player is physically show the shuffle of these cards gives him opportunity to follow how the cards move and can eliminate possibilities.Also every encounter with ""red spot"" on it, is part of a quest of sorts. When dealt with correctly will unlock the next part of the quest available for your encounter deck. This is very neat way of not making the game all about getting to the boss but the path to the boss is also important.So that this review would not be complete hype lets bring up few issues:-Combat is every now and then very easy. When there are 1-4 opponents you can overwhelm the enemy quickly because your ""auto targeting"" attacks send you flying across the map. You feel like juggernaut from Dota 2-Block / Counter animations are too slow compared to your normal ones. You feel like everyone in the game stops for your to do your animation.-Enemies NEVER attack at same time. There is always only single enemy swinging a sword + one ranged enemy ready to fire.-Block / Counter ""quick-time"" prompts show for too long. I feel like being babied into the game. I wish there was some difficulty settings about this.-Blood. Game really needs blood right now the swings rarely give me that satisfaction. I barely get any feedback from hitting the enemy. Its even harder to discern how much damage I've done or have I actually killed one of my enemies without any blood splatters.As you can see Most gripes I have are in the combat of the game. Thankfully the combat still feels fun but could be more.And HEY! It's not all about the combat anyway. :3"
