,Recommended,266510,17342648,"Posted: 1 August, 2015",all,Coronaxe,"Hand of Fate is really something out of the ordinary;Designed as a card collecting/dungeon brawler game, it tries a fresh, new approach to both genres.+-Interesting gameplayGreat voice actingAmazing artworkVery forgiving, yet challengingOne-button combatsluggish animations in combatDescription to how the game works; (thought I'd put it a bit after the pro and cons, as it's a bit mundane to read.)At the start of each new dungeon, you'll get to choose, which cards are in your own ""equipment"" deck and which cards you want to add to the dealer's deck. So you decide whether you want this extra shield or ring, or rather add an extra sword into the deck. The same thing is possible with your dealer's deck, as it's your call to make your game easier and miss out on those card tokens, which you need for new cards, equipment as well as encounters, or choose the cards, which are yet to be beaten and try your best on the way.The dealer lays out a dungeon with the chosen cards, in which you navigate around with your little figurine, kinda like a board game. From time to time you'll encounter a monster or a trap, from where the game will switch into a Arkam City-style 3rd person combat system, which is debateably the weakest part of the game, in which you can move around a small area, dodge, attack and counter attacks.I really hope you found this review helpful in aiding your decision towards buying this game.If you have thoughts on improving this review, please contact me! (:"
