,Recommended,266510,17760705,"Posted: 28 August, 2015",all,Mitch,"Hand of Fate is perfect for fans of card games, deck-building, and role-playing games.   Questlines are randomly generated from a mix of cards owned by both you and the dealer.  Playing through the game rewards you with more cards to add into your decks.  While in a quest, you need to manage your health, money, and food.  You will encounter enemies, allies, and obstacles in your quests and they're always presented to you with choices similar to FTL: Faster than Light.There's also an element of chance that goes along with your decisions.  An example could be that you're walking along a cliff, and you see a sword at the bottom among some bones.  Do you go on your way or try and climb down? If you try to climb down, you then have to watch four cards, with varying degrees of success or failure on them, be shuffled on-screen.  You pick your card and either get injured on your climb down, or succeed and get the sword (which you can then use in combat).  Combat encounters throw you into a room with enemies and the game turns into a simple version of the Arkham Batman games. The fighting is very similar with it's use of blocking, countering, and combos.As of the writing of this review, the game is currently 50% off! It's still worth the purchase at full-price though."
76561197983225082,Recommended,266510,16688596,"Posted: 24 June, 2015",all,baddog993,"I first became aware of this game on WFT is Hand of fate. I loved the art style and the Batman like fighting style. Some people dont really care for the Batman style. Basically its one button to punch and one to block one button to stun and one other button to dogdge. I enjoy this because its easy to understand and easy to pick up on and it looks really good for the most part. The game has a deck of cards and you have a piece that you move around the cards. Differents cards have different stuff inside of them.So for instance a card could contain a weapon of some sort after going down a ravine. The game is very well written and the guy who is the dungeon master looks and sounds great. So for fighting its sometimes one card and sometimes its 2 card with enemies. Sometimes its a boss plus more enemies. However fear not because the game gives you power ups.Via armor and weapons. Some have fire and some have stuns. Also you can get poisin for weapons or stuns or sometimes you can get the knife card that flies in 8 different directions. GOod stuff. I really like the graphics of this game even the fight scene are enjoyable. Watching that slow motion final death blow to an enemy always makes me smile. Even more so if its a boss that  I kill.You can also re arrange the deck or have the computer do it for you. If your wondering how to change the gameplay like I was. Go into the deck building part and click on the middle card and here you can select different cards that can change the game rules its also comes in handy for the dlc. I am playing the monk card right now.So graphics are very sharp looking, sounds are good. My complaints about the game are few. Sometimes you can get a lousy hand and either die because of bad drops or no food. I am halfway done with the game so it seems like it might be a tad short. Maybe around 12 or 15 hours long? Perhaps less it does have an endless mode.Some on the forum have complained of the game being too dark after they switched to the newer unity engine. I have not had this issue and they did roll back the changes but some are still having issues. The fix right now is windowed mode.My only other nit pick is sometimes the traps are a real pain. You fight in rooms and some are small and some are big and loaded with traps. It does hurt the bad guys as well however. So thats fair. I am having a good time with the game and I really enjoy it. One more thing the developers seem to be very active on the forums and seem to care so thats a very good thing.A fun and unique game. Most games  last around 10minutes up to 20 minutes or perhaps a little longer. Not super long. Buy it and you can thank me later."
