76561197965282243,Recommended,266510,17440791,"Posted: 8 August, 2015",all,Hatch,"I got attached toHand of Fatepretty quick.  It's a real fun role-play card game.  Basically you're sitting across the table of a card dealer or dungeon master, however you see it.  He deals you cards and that determines what enemies you fight, where you fight and items you get.  You also gain loot by chance by flipping cards or winning fights.  Sometimes there's a character on a card and you can select answers when they speak.  Unlike other card games, when the level and enemies have been drawn you're character is warped into that world and you really fight them!  I've found that the controls are just like the Batman Arkham series when using Xbox controller.  The game is fun right from the start and easy to figure out.ProsCard game and battle adventure gameEasy to learnGame outcome depends on cards drawn and player choiceGraphicsControlsConsPretty difficult at the end.  Most of the game plays easy but the ending can be unfair.Lack of game info.  While the game is easy to learn I wish it had an info page to give a breakdown on what everything does to serve as a reminder.  Like what cards do what, the rules on food, buying and selling, etc.  You just have to pick up on it as you play."
