,Recommended,266510,19985270,"Posted: 26 December, 2015",all,cheesegod,"This game was in my Steam library. I have no idea how it got there. Maybe it was a hasty purchase during a sale, maybe it was from a humble bundle, maybe a friend gifted it to me. However it got in my library, I'm glad it did.This game is a hybrid roguelike and card game. It sounds like a weird combo, but it works well. Your path through the dungeon is randomly laid out cards on the board. When the card is flipped over, sometimes you'll have to battle a monster, figure your way through a short story or even play a mini game. Many cards have a requirement, once you meet that requirement you get a token that unlocks more cards for your deck. Each time you play, you add more and more options for future games.Some of the cards, however, rely on chance. I personally don't mind that but I know some people might find that offputting. The monster battles are in real time, which is cool. They're a bit on the easy side, however. Those are minor gripes, if you like roguelikes or TCGs or both you should check this game out."
