,Recommended,266510,20234144,"Posted: 2 January, 2016",all,catwhowalksbyhimself,"This is a strange little game.  It incorporates elements of cards games, rpg games, and action style games and tries to wield them all together.  It shouldn't work, but somehow it does, creating something refreshingly different.The core of the games main story mode is that you pick a boss to go after (although you must beat each to go on to the next one) the assemble a deck of story cards and one of equipment.  The story cards are then mixed together with new cards by the mysterious Dealer and laid out to form a map.  As you move your character onto a story card, it flips over, usually resulting in a choose your own adventure style encounter, although there are also straight up combats and stores to discover.  Any equipment you find is usually drawn from your equipment deck, so what cards you put in that can be important as are what encounters you added into the mix. Some encounter cards come with tokens you can earn by achieving something during the encounter.WIn or lose, once your run is over, any tokens you've earned unlock new eqiupment and encounter cards.  It is no coincidence that some of the most useful cards are rewards for some of the most risky encounters, so going safe is not always good for the long run.Combat is handled with a battle system nearly identical to the Batman Arkham games.  If you enjoyed that system, you'll like this one.All in all a very unique game that is easy to pick up for a quick 30 minute run."
