76561198101843053,Recommended,266510,20851060,"Posted: 30 January, 2016",all,ObsidianBeard ( . Y . ),"This game is super AWESOME and fun!And it gets increasingly better value for money as time goes on!How is that even possible? you may ask: well this already fleshed out fully immersive game, keeps having more content added into it every month or so:I stopped playing for a couple months, come back and start playing, die in a dungeon yet again and am rewarded by unlocking 2 new DLC that got added without my knowing, Fantastic!The narrator/dealer of the game makes it such an awesomly immersive experiance, each step has a chance to get further dialogue.GAMEPLAY:Before statring a run;You have 2 decks of cards you can change up with your unlocked cards: 1st your equipment, 2nd your exploration/encounters. The dealer adds further encounter cards based on the level, of which there are 12.3rd deck option if you paid for it (which is a must, so worth, so good): is picking a class/difficulty for you character, that can affect combat and exploration, including unlocking more encounter cards.Each run attempt you can select different things for those 3 options, and each attempt will unlock more cards for your main 2 mentioned decks.3 resorces that needs various degrees of management and affect you are; HEALTH, FOOD, GOLD.Exploration:the cards are aranged face down in a path, you move 1 card at a time, flippping it over and selecting options to get through it. could be a fight, merchant, chance, or choice based options.The results can be anything from many of these cards, most of them have a chance to unlock further cards for future attempts, if you select correctly/choose well. Through these is the main way of drawing from your equipment deck and affecting your 3 resorces.The whole time the dealer has awesome dialogue based on the cards and your options as well as banter, this makes the atmospher of the game awesome.Combat:Is fairly simple but fun and can be heavily affected by equpitment, blessings and curses you have got hold of during that run. You have attack, combo damage, block,counter, stun, dodge roll, weapon ability, artifact ability.This from an overall perspective is a very unique and fun game, plenty of loot and replayablity, and you gain more options even on failing a run, so your time never feels completely wasted.VERDICT:There's nothing about the game I dislike or feel is badly done, so a full recommendation from me :)"
,Recommended,266510,20887098,"Posted: 31 January, 2016",all,ClintostheGreat,"For those of you who would rather watch my video review, here ya go:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zcdq-eYCgXEWhat this game did well was make a very replayable game with an interesting story that makes you want to keep replaying it. It does this through the side stories in the game. For a lot of cards, when you land on them they will give you a side quest that you can complete. If you do complete it then it will unlock another card that keeps driving this side story into multiple play throughs. This really helps in making the game not stagnate the more you play it, because it is constantly adding new cards for you to interact with and furthering the stories at the same time.On the subject of RNG, this game is not always fair because a lot of it comes down to RNG. Most of the time you can handle what the game throws at you, but sometimes you will have a game where literally nothing goes your way. If you do not enjoy games that have RNG elements like this, then you will probably not enjoy this game. However, I feel like for the most part the RNG is not that bad.The main problem that this game has is the combat. The combat is fairly simplistic, where you mainly just dodge and counter enemy attacks, similar to the Batman Arkham games, but less polished. Something about the combat just isn’t very satisfying. The enemies usually take a good bit of hits before they go down and when they do go down they don’t really have any kind of death animation, they just go full ragdoll which isn’t very gratify.But, this game is still very enjoyable to play and I recommend checking it out."
