76561198018474955,Recommended,266510,20884924,"Posted: 31 January, 2016",all,Grayson,"Excellent game with an incredibly interesting concept, and solid execution. Cards become your gear, encounters, everything, and many of them have tokens. By succeeding at that card's encounter, you get the token, which create new cards for future games. I'm playing the Story mode, and it's fantastic. I've progressively unlocked a bunch of different new stories that I'm encountering in future games.You choose your equipment and some of the encounter cards to build each match, and then the story setup you've selected adds cards. It's clever and works well.Most cards are choices rather than combat, with semi-random success, others are static choices that you can learn and rely on in future games. This creates a great mix of surprise and predictability.Combat is fairly basic but engaging - not the highlight of the game, but it doesn't hurt it either.Story mode (Guessing 6-8 hours playtime), endless-play mode, and then modifiers that change the way some things work."
