76561198262678463,Recommended,266510,20565214,"Posted: 16 January, 2016",all,Nevarine,"Just 100%ed the game and it's dlc wildcards. I'll focus on the main game in this review. This game is well worth the price(although I got it during the winter sale). The replayablity is really high and there are tons of new cards to unlock everytime you play a stage or endless. The main game let's you select the boss for the stage and each one comes with seperate rules(in the form of curses) and encounters to make getting to each boss it's own challenge. You can make your own deck to suit your playstyle or to adapt to certain stages, the cards that make up the equipment and encounter deck are cards you unlock from bosses, tokens, and from the easy and hard mode fates(you also unlock new gain cards from tokens). Equipment explains it's self, but encounter cards make up the floors in the stages, so you are in charge of the events that occur on each floor, it's a really awesome feature of this game. There are three main ways to die, one is from combat, another is from failing chance cards that make you draw pain cards, and last is from starvation.The combat in the game isn't the best part, but it at least provides a good amount of challenge to the game, this is even more so if you're stuck in basic gear. Some negative things I could say about the game would be some chance cards are really hard to succeed at or survive(looking at you Petward ;c) and some of the most annoying encounters are locked in your deck and can ruin a playthrough. I'll briefly go over endless which is a mode where you select which fate you'll use and every card you unlocked will be in the mode(so no deck building), it's pretty much a mode where you need to survive as long as possible to get a highscore. Endless can be fun, but if you have encounters like Petward still up it could be all for naught. So I would highly recommend this game to anyone who likes rogue-likes and action rpgs that have a twist to make it feel like a completely different experience. :)"
