76561197997032269,Recommended,266510,31252443,Posted: 20 April,all,The_Emperror,"TL;DR - There is absolutely nothing bad I can say about this game. It's a bit slow, but it fits the game. There's a lot of reading, but it fits the game - it's a ""choose your own adventure"" type game. It's amazing. Strongly, very strongly recommended.Positives:1. Atmosphere. It's really well made. It's consistent with it's themes and atmosphere, the ambient noises, dark visuals, hand drawn beautiful cards, etc etc.2. Presentation. Amazing. The way your avatar appears on the battlefield from a card, the way each item appears from the cards... The way randomness is made - you pick a card from a shuffled deck. Great ideas, and implemented very well...3. Variety. This game is a huge mix of CCG, RPG, Dungeon Crawler, Action Adventure, Exploration, etc etc etc... There is so much to do, there are so many different things to do, and all that is hidden so well in the cards and general gameplay mechanics...4. Visuals. Yeah, it's not as great visually as Crysis or Witcher 3 or whatever. Still, the visual art style is fitting, consistent and overall really great looking, and that's the most important for visuals - to look good.5. Gameplay. That is kinda covered in the variety point, but again, you are playing a choose your own Dungeon Crawling adventure CCG with RPG elements, customizable equipment and fighting style, as well as doing quest chains, mini quest chains, beating guys up, well, everything.6. The Dealer. Oh, the dealer... I will leave it at that. The dealer.???1. The game is a bit slow, but it have a lot of reading. So it's understandable. I don't consider it a negative, but some people may dislike the slow progression speed. Some rounds can go WAY over an hour if you read every encounter..2. There is a lot of reading. A LOT of reading. The writing is good, which helps, but still, there is a lot of text, that needs to be crunched. After a few rounds some basic cards will start repeating themselves, so repetition may become an issue. I still don't consider that a negative, but some people may not enjoy the literature aspects as much as me."
