,Recommended,266510,16590994,"Posted: 21 June, 2015",all,Fox01313,"Quite fun as a mix of a board game & card game in mechanics with a bit of combat thrown in. Highly addictive game where you assemble a deck of cards on what you might encounter for equipment or encounters with the stranger you are playing against has his own cards to throw against you. From there the cards you pick for encounters are put out in a path for each section where sometimes you have a choice & others it's a straight path.Sometimes it's more of a 3rd person adventure style of combat against different opponents, other times with the encounters, you are given cards that have various success & failure, take your pick & your gains or losses will sometimes unlock new cards adding to the addictive nature of the game. Blessings & curses are random later on to make things quite a challenge as you gain new tactics to use or avoid to help you on your quest. From the unlocked cards, you can go back to battle old bosses with the added challenge of taking new cards in to make a familiar encounter completely new depending on the cards you get from what you picked. Highly recommended."
76561198008928472,Recommended,266510,18285269,"Posted: 1 October, 2015",all,AdvisingBob,"-Straight playthrough can probably take several hours (depending on difficulty). Even though I went through one playthrough, I was left pretty satisfied.A pretty entertaining adventure game that involves cards and chance. You set up two decks that involve cards of scenarios you can encounter and the equipment you can receive during your adventure. As you progress through the game, you unlock more cards and can build larger decks and have a greater variety of situations and items to experience. While the game does have a diffuclty option, in a way, the way you customize your deck can add an entirely new dimension of diffuclty to the game. Personally, that mechanic is probably what stood out the most. Even if you are playing a high difficulty, you could fill your decks with scenarios that could make things a bit easier. Of course, still expect the game overall and all of its aspects to be challenging, you choose a high difficulty overall. Combat system of arena combat is a nice break from selecting and reading cards.The game has the means to produce several playthroughs, difficulty, classes, or trying to experience all the given scenarios."
