76561197971028644,Recommended,266510,19193288,"Posted: 21 November, 2015",all,Слепострел,"The arrival of cards is barely balanced out. Such uncommon game mechanics can be fun but mostly frustrating. As a player you feel very detached from what is going on since you can't influence anything (either encounters or you can't go back to a previous level or you can't even heal yourself and the story is almost non-existent). This game is a feast of randomness. You can get a tough fight and almost useless reward or vice versa. Or you can get several hard fights in a row. The game can plant a couple of mini-bosses into a regular fight. Another session you may get a boss fight just one card away from the start armed only with basic equipment.What kept me playing was the melee system which resembled very much the one of Batman: Arkham Trilogy.Overall, it's a brilliant time-waster and it's worth taking a look because of its game mechanics. But most likely it'll be a short look."
