,Recommended,266510,19378679,"Posted: 29 November, 2015",all,travislaborde,"I've not seen another game like this before, but I hope it is the first of many.  I'm really liking this game a lot.It is a ""deck building"" game, with a  great twist - the deck is used to generate an ""adventure"" for you to experience.  The cards are laid out (at random?) for you to go over, one by one.  Some cards will give you equipment or other aid, some will give you battles to fight.When you DO fight, it is action combat on a small battlefield.  Lots of mad clicking and pressing going on.  Great animations, the ""slow down camera"" for big hits and battle endings.  All that jazz.The only CON I can say so far is that it is a little annoying sometimes in how the randomness affects things.  An example goes like this:   After a fight which you've one, it might say ""one of the enemies is only faking his death"" and offer you the choice - go back and get him, or leave him be.  It shows you 4 cards - 3 with success and 1 with failure.  It shuffles those and you pick one.  Lots of scenarios like that, and it seems to come up with the ""bad"" card way too often.The game has many ways for you to alter the difficulty UP or DOWN, and from what I've seen so far, it will have a huge amount of replayability.I love it!"
,Recommended,266510,19425722,"Posted: 1 December, 2015",all,Ybalrid,"This is a deck building roguelike RPG with anawesomeart direction.Each ""level"" is a series of cards drawn on the table. You're represented as a golden pawn that cah go to the verry next cards. Each card is an encounter. It can be good for you, bad for you, test your luck (or ability to not be fooled...) or oblige you to fight.Your equipement are cards. You earn token that unlocks more cards. Every random aspect of the game is handeled by cards.The compat system makes it an action-RPG. The combat mechanices are the same as in the recent Batman games and it's really pleasing.From a Game Design standpoint it's a little marvel. I urge you to try it out!"
