76561198014485375,Recommended,266510,19477807,"Posted: 4 December, 2015",all,Mad hatters in jeans,"This game is just so much fun to play. Even after unlocking most of the cards there's still new things you can do with the game. Different ways to play, different decisions to make with the kinds of gear your earn in each level. The combat is also quite satisfying if a little clunky at times.The dealer, (basically the narrator or DM if you're used to DnD) has a fantastic voice and lines for each of the cards you play. He'll make funny and sarcastic comments based on if you're doing well, or poorly. This adds to the atmosphere so much that I wish they have the dealer more lines to say.This game currently has two game modesStoryWhere you unlock cards as you progress through the game, with various boss fights thrown in here and there.I believe this is the best game mode for learning how to play, it gets you used to how the game functions and furthermore you can alter your ""deck"" of cards you take into each encounter. Along with some of the cards you'll face as well.EndlessThis is where things get interesting for me. Although the story mode is great, it just doesn't have the pure sense of rolling the dice.As Endless combines all of the cards you've unlocked and throws them into random encounters, with each level advanced in this mode you'll either face an encounter/recieve a curse or both.But eventually the game just throws some really powerful pain cards at you and you have no choice but to lose. (This is only once you get to about level 30, which is quite difficult even with the right equipment found/bought.)Along with some free dlc they've recently released for this game it really is a lot of fun to play and learn how to beat various encounters.I have a lot of fun playing this game and the devs are very active on the forums.I definitely recommend this game."
,Recommended,266510,19584416,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,Novahot,"Hand Of Fate, not so family friendly Fantasy card game with real time combat. I love the game, I have beaten almost all of the bosses (stuck on the last one) and I love how hard the game is!My first expressions to Hand of fate were something like this: ""Another fantasy card game? Hearthstone ripp-off?"" But I was suprised how there is third-person realtime combat in this! So how does it work?The idea is this: There is the ""table"" where you have cards. You don't know what the cards are and as you move you unfold the cards one by one. Behind every card there could be a Fight, a choice, a shop or the Devil giving you something to kill. The more you play the more cards you get, and more cards you have, more difficult the game gets. Also the first time you kill a boss, it becomes a reqular encounter in the game. So don't be like me and say ""Now I will never have to fight him again.."" WoopsieThe game is wonderful and I recommend it from my frozen heart,,, now I have a meeting with the King of Scales (again)"
