,Recommended,266510,19558351,"Posted: 7 December, 2015",all,Peregrine_Caged,"The game may not be everyone's cup of tea, but if it matches your personality and what you like, look out. I don't have a lot of hours on record yet--mostly because it's a little hard on my outdated laptop--but I fully expect that number to skyrocket. It's everything I could want and more, despite being a relatively simple game.Which is why I say it's likely not for everyone. The gameplay is very straightforward. There's not much to it. If you get bored easily, it might not be more than a time waster for you (and a possibly pricey one). At worst, you may grow tired of it completely.For me, though, I can't get enough. Granted, as a Dungeon Master, it really taps into my sense of adventure designing. Even though you come across the same cards and do the same things, it's still delightfully interesting thinking on how things interact and work to bring you where you are. Every play is a different adventure, and that appeals to me.And though the gameplay is relatively simple, that also means that it's very solid. While there's some luck to it, admittedly, I still feel like I am in control. When I lose, it's my fault, when I win, it's because I planned well.All in all, I am incredibly pleased. For the adventure lovers, for those who kind of like coming up with their own story with a vaguer backbone, this is for you. For the rest... I dunno, go watch somebody play for a bit, and decide for yourself."
,Recommended,266510,19589689,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,The Immortal Beaver,"It's a turn-based roguelike card-game with realtime combat, a tremendous amount of replayability, and a fantastic atmosphere that brilliantly mixes the creepiness of the dealer with the thrill of a fantastical adventure. The writing is wonderful, and engine updates have made the game visually excellent by most any standards. It's a brilliant game, and easily one of the best of the year.The cherry on top? The developers are wonderful. A long time back when the game was still in early access, someone complained about a spider that would crawl around on the table at random times during play. I fired the game up recently to check out the (completely free and quite extensive) Christmas updates, scrolled through the options to see if anything was different, and noticed an option to turn the spider off. These guys are the best, and if the game interests you, they absolutely deserve your money."
,Recommended,266510,19877378,"Posted: 23 December, 2015",all,Kraege,"Part board game, part card game, part RPG and part action game. Create two sets of cards. One set is of items to find. The other set is of encounters. Thankfully the NPC (game master?) shuffles and sorts everything out for you.The GM places cards on the table in various configurations and you move a taoken along the cards as you would on a grid or board. Sometimes you have more than one direction from which to choose. Most often you can only more in one direction. Once chosen you reveal the card to see what you encounter. You may encounter combat, find equipment, make a choice as to your action or many others. Don't forget to stock up on food as each card your token moves to will cost one food.After traveling awhile (down stairs to new 'floors'), you find the end boss. Use your equipment to defeat this foe the same way you beat any previous combat. Use the ASWD keys to swing your current weapon. Other items may give you other skills and will be explained as you get them. If you beat the boss, you'll unlock many new cards and can change your decks around to include them if you wish.Tailor your decks to what you think might happen. Add more armor, a shield or even stronger weapons. There is a lot you cannot plan for, so I suggest erring on the side of caution.You can always go into another 'dungeon' to fight a boss you have already fought. To start a game, choose the boss you want to fight then choose the difficulty for what is needed to unlock specials. No spoiler given here.Good luck and no matter what the GM says, don't turn back"
