,Recommended,266510,16607698,"Posted: 21 June, 2015",all,madSimon,"Really enjoyable, fresh concept. You're essentially playing through mini campaigns where each time you encounter a card, you progress the story and potentially earn rewards.The deck building is odd at first, but you slowly beging to favor certain cards as you play.There is some luck involved with random card draws and choices, but you can actually watch the choice cards as they shuffle on the screen.The combat encounters are well done with the enemies you fight generated from the cards drawn. A ""4 of Skulls"" will have you fighting 4 skeletons, for example. Combat resembles a simplified Arkham Batman system with combos, counters, and abilities based on your weapons and shields.Very polished with lots of subtle touches in the environments and animations. Plenty of challenge due to the randomness and multiple difficulty levels."
