,Recommended,266510,14650858,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,Hikelos,"Overall a very enjoyable experience.The story unfolds through the cards, giving little glimpses of a plot that the game leaves to your interpretation.The combat in itself is pretty basic, but then again, there sholdn't even be action combat in this kind of game, so it comes off as a very nice breath of fresh air from the standard rogue-like game.The soundtrack is pretty sweet, the sound effects are never exxagerated or annoying and the dealer's voice is just perfect.The only really bad side of this game is in the last 2-3 story runs:While the game ups its difficulty by adding new cards and mechanics and presenting you with choices for its full (very enjoyable) duration, the last runs, especially the final run, is completely based on RNG and there is absolutely nothing you can do about it. You try and die countless times until you finally get that perfect run where everything just runs smoothly.However, that is only true for the last story run, the whole game is really enjoyable and the Endless Mode gives some pretty nice replayability.[Possible Spoilers Do not read further]The game ends in the most abrupt manner.You beat the Dealer, screen goes black, you're back at the starting screen.No cheeky comment, no ending, no nothing.It ends so badly that i actually thought i experienced a glitch, that some cutscene of some sort just got jumped for some reason, but that doesn't seem to be the case.And honestly after the phisical torture that is the last Story Run, i at least wanted some insight on the Dealer, the Player, the game, something, ANYTHING, but it just didn't happen and it tastes so bitter."
