,Recommended,266510,28770978,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,sleepeh yukeh,"An excellet game. Simply put. I recieved this as a christmas present from my boyfriend and was instantly hooked until i managed to finish it.quick trait list: singleplayer, but the kind of game that's perfect for playing with someone watching, wether that be your girlfriend/partner, child, younger sibling or anything similar.witty dialogue and narrative. It's casually funny, you probably wont be coughing with laughter but it'll likely get you chuckling quite a bit. Depends on your sense of humour.Gameplay is quick, simple and yet unforgiving - its as easy to slip up and die as it is to spam down squads of enemies with repetitive, effective attacks.THE GAME:The game is a bit similar to Hand of Fate, though with more world-wandering and less decision making. Each level has multiple paths you can take to reach the goal.It may also resemble rogue-lites like FTL.Plot: The game has a surprisingly fun plot behind it. I wont say too much to avoid spoiling it, but if you're a fan of time-traveling (or seeing into the future) you are going to like it.The game has very fluid gameplay, with a few, luckily minor bugs. The art style resembles the ""golden age"" of video games, that is to say games between 1990 and 2010. Very charming art style, amazing narrator (that comments randomly from time to time, on almost all your actions - even just spinng around in circles.)The game is also CHOCK FULL OF REFERRENCES! It draws many parallels to Star Wars, while referencing a plethora of other video games and movies - both more modern games and older movies alike.Very intelligent writing, witty and light-hearted. At the same time, the events that happens and the story itself is hypocriticaly dark for such a light-hearted narration. The gameplay itself has a style that could fit for a game playable by most ages (think the newer spyro trilogy, before the series went to♥♥♥♥♥♥ and features a somewhat restricted but still fun crafting system, akin to games like Jak & Daxter and Sphinx.There are A LOT of different endings here. I wont spoil."
