,Recommended,266510,16908349,"Posted: 6 July, 2015",all,Moobabe,"One of my biggest issues with roguelikes as a genre, and I know it's counter intuitive given its a staple of it, is the lack of permanent progression and the sheer despair of wasted time when you die. We are busy people and yes, roguelikes are fun and challenging, but many simply don't respect the time of the player. Hate of Fate does. Even when you die you'll still be rewarded for the tokens that you've unlocked to that point so more cards are added to your deck, while each chapter is only, at most, 20 minutes long. By making the roguelike a little more accessible the team at Defiant Development have made a game worthy of taking both your time and money.http://www.permanent-beta.net/reviews-1/2015/6/26/hand-of-fate"
