,Recommended,266510,12195136,"Posted: 22 September, 2014",all,CryonicSuspension,"Updated: 7th July, 2015I love this game and want to have the Australian developers' kangaroo babies.The game mechanics are difficult to explain, since I've never seen any game like this. You get to pick half of the cards that will appear in the game ( your favourite weapons, armour and positive encounters ), the computer picks the other half ( rusty weapons, monsters, curses and negative encounters ).The computer shuffles your deck with his deck, this creates true procedural generation. No two games will ever be the same. The cards are placed, so as to simulate floors in a building and corridors.This is Kenuty's excellent Early Access gamplay video:http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XRc6O9HeP6wThe combat for the first few quests consisted of simple attack and parry but scaled up to ""God of War 1"" meets ""Golden Axe"" with: tumble, shield bash, magical weapons and magical artifacts.There are 12 different quests. It took me 20 hours to finish three quarters of the game ( at which point I had only unlocked a little over half of the equipment cards and half of the encounter cards ie. the game is massive ). It took me another 20 hours to finish the last three missions because they are brutal. I highly recommend this game to hardcore gamers!If you want to make the game easier or harder, there is a ""Wildcards"" expansion that will do that:http://store.steampowered.com/app/350460/The voice narration is eloquent. I thought that it was narrated by Jeremy Irons but it was voiced by Anthony Skordi. The dialogue is immersive and teaches you the game mechanics on the fly, as you encounter the different cards.Northern Lion: ""Let's Look At: Hand of Fate!""https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pLSEOkX83yE"
