76561198111876156,Recommended,266510,26061771,"Posted: 15 October, 2016",all,JACS,keyi
,Recommended,266510,16863288,"Posted: 3 July, 2015",all,crowbar,"rating: worth buying at sale price (<7.5€)score: 7.5/10 - goodsimilar games: FTL, Batman Arkham (combat system)tags: pen & paper, unique presentation, rogue-liteThe biggest problem I have with this game is the balancing. I immediately started the game in hard mode and I still beat every boss in my first try until the last row of bosses. Here it started to get hard, but only because of randomness and chances. Either the game gives you crazy curses or just some tiny things which dont really make it more challenging for you, there is not much inbetween. Also the blessings you get are nowhere near as powerful as the curses you get, most of the blessings are simply useless. Later there will be many encounters which outcome is either you get to draw 3 equipment cards or something like that, or you loose 50% of your maximum health. Again there is nothing in between. Why not loose 5% maximum health? Why maximum health? Why not normal health? Ah because the game lets you regenerate tons of health every step so making you loose health isn't a problem, but when you are out of rations you loose TONS of health with every step. They should reduce both of these values and make the punishments less ridiculous.At this part of the game it's not about ""do I want to take this event with me or not"" but more about ""just try to pass every card without getting into trouble"". What makes this more problematic are the rewards you get. Most of the time it's just things like ""+5 max health"" (WOW!), ""+5 gold"" (WOW!) and after you found a good weapon or good armor all other armor or weapon drops you get are useless. At least you can wear many rings at the same time, so those are always useful, but the rings don't have good effects at all, some totally useless. And even worse, every reward you get is meant for combat, but not the game itself, like there is nothing which gives you better chances or I don't know more vision of the map or something like that apart from 1 or 2 items maybe.And this is a problem because the combat in this game is extremely easy, I beat 90% of the fights without loosing health, and if I loose health it's just because I got careless because it's so easy. So if the game gives me stuff which makes combat even easier I'm not really feeling rewarded.The combat itself is solid, but they throw in so many unnessary and random slow motions during the fight which are annoying and bad for the pacing. There aren't that many different enemy types but enough I guess. Whats nice is that the different weapons and armors do not simply have better or worse stats, but unique effects like ""cast an explosion"", ""freeze everyone"", ""damage everyone who hits you"" and stuff like that.My problem with the combat is that it doesn't fit the theme of the game in my opinion. This is a card game, so I thought it is the perfect situation for a combat like in other card games like Hearthstone, Yu-gi-oh or whatever. Or make a turn-based fighting system which happens on the table with the cards. Everything is better than what we have here, especially because this Arkham combat system is only as good as its presentation, you need nice sound effects, lots of great animations and stuff like that.The biggest selling point is the presentation of the game, I especially like the ""gamemaster"". Unfortunately he starts to repeat himself very fast and very often which gets annoying. But the voice actor does a good job. Also the music fits the game and creates a nice atmossphere, but you will hear the same music all the time. The card texts are written very well and there is a good amount of variety. I like that they want to tell small sub-stories within the game, after beating a card you get its symbol which unlocks a new card which continues the story of the previous card in some way. But they could do more with that, because these cards still work individually and tell smaller stories than I expected. I think what would be nice is that you could have like 4 cards for the same story which you could all put in your deck, then the game would scatter them in the world in order and you get better and better rewards for each of them. This would give you more decisions as the player, do you put the beginning cards of the story in your deck which is safer or do you put more story cards in your deck to have like more synergy. Currently the deck building is bare bones. I just put everything in my deck where I haven't unlocked the symbol yet and the rest I fill up with the cards where I know the game won`t screw me over, because some cards are just useless. The chances of winning for some is ridiculous and the rewards are not good enough at all to make this risk worth it.The game is still fun because of the nice presentation, exploring the different cards and their stories and the combat is not terrible, but doesn`t fit the game. Some design flaws and some wasted potential makes this just a ""good"" game though, but it could easily be a fantastic game."
