76561198014921375,Not Recommended,266510,14531998,"Posted: 18 February, 2015",all,cosmicandre,"This game is good...not great. Hopefully with some dev tweaks - it could be really excellent.It's very innovative and well done. Graphics are pleasant, the concept is refreshing and the execution is...well...it's ok.Some of the positives:1) Great concept. This is a card game and a button masher. It's not an RPG. There's no levelling of your character, no stats to decide in which to invest, no classes, no abilities.  It's a card game that unfolds into button mashing sequences based on the cards that are randomly drawn. The mix of card and action elements combined with a fantasy/D&D type setting are neat and are done well.2) The game is polished. The graphics are nice, the voice acting is very good, the presentation of the encounters are well done, etc. It's a well put together game with nice artwork, GUI, sounds, etc.Some of the negatives:1) The cards PART 1. For me , I dislike the card designs greatly. The devs chose to go with a basic brown card with black text - and it's drab. The rest of the game is graphically very colorful and interesting. I realize the card design is going for an old parchment feel - but it just seems uninteresting to me. I could have done with some interesting edge work, slight color tints, or edging...something. There are tons of card games out there and the cards themselves are always something of great time and effort in the design , sometimes even with collector editions, gold versions , etc.2) The cards PART 2. For some reason, the devs thought it would be interesting to ""lock"" cards. When you get them, you don't know what they do until you come across them in your journey. This makes the whole part where you get cards at the end of your journey nearly pointless. When you complete a card/journey, you can get a token , and at the conclusion of a journey your tokens are exchanged for cards. The cards turn over on your screen and all you can do is look at the title and picture and wonder what they do....unless it's something you already unlocked. Perhaps this is fun to others and not to me, but I compare to Hearthstone - when you open a new pack - you can instantly read the description of the card - and start understanding if you should be excited about it or not. For a portion of the game where I feel getting new cards should be very rewarding and exciting - it's not. It's actually quite tedious as I have to turn in all my tokens, get my cards (which I don't know what they do) and that leads me to #3.3) Deck building. The same issue rears its head in building your deck. You can have many cards that are locked - that you don't know what they do - but if you want to know what they do - you put them in - hope to draw them during a journey - and hope you like it. That's really not a design choice that is rewarding to me.4) Help. The game is easy to grasp once you play - but at the start - nothing is explained - and there is no good on screen help. An example are the tokens. It wasn't at all clear that a token was on the card, and that upon completing that card - you get the token - and that at the conclusion of the journey and beating the boss - that you get all the tokens you collected along the way and turn them in for cards. It also wasn't clear initially that you lose food each time you move, or gain health each time you move. You learn this super fast, but a tiny popup or something would be good. In fact, there's a couple different token shapes - still not sure the differences between them all.5) Easy + Repetitive. The game is fun, but so far, it's very repetitive. After just a couple journeys - I've run across the same cards over and over. It's also the same pattern - card, battle...card, battle. The battles are also the same for me...roll, x,x,x....roll, x,x,x....roll,x,x,x.....win.  I'm about half done with the game, maybe it gets more complex , but so far -it hasn't.In summary, it's a neat game...it's solid. There could be more done with the cards and the deck building to make it more interactive, but its repetitive and the card element isn't rewarding enough to compensate.Update: Saw there is DLC 1 month after release - so , since game is decent, but was on the fence, am going with not reccomended since DLC immediately after release is a money grab."
