76561197997028084,Not Recommended,266510,26170020,"Posted: 22 October, 2016",all,taviyo,"The critical foundation of any fantasy card game is the strategic use of cards. It's the development of your own customized deck. Combining cards in your customized deck to provide multipliers in combination with other cards, for use against a specific opponent. Hand of Fate is the most perfect name for this game because literally there is no strategy in developing your own deck, it's all left to Fate.Issues-Right off the bat, getting the chance to pull an equipment card is so rare, the whole point of having a customized deck is almost useless.The default size of your customized deck grows every level, decreasing the chances of you pulling any one card. For instance, I believe the start deck size is near 20 cards and since the chance of getting an equipment card to pull is less than once per level, this means the chance of pulling any one card is less than 5%.It's almost as if the dev's intentionally made the user deck larger as you advance levels, as a way to nerf the effectiveness of the cards and having a customizable card deck, in an attempt to make the game more difficult and stretch the game out. If this is the case, it's a bloody shame because its sacrificing crutial gameplay in an attempt to balance.If you guys want to play a really good card game then I suggest going to Pokemon or Hearthstone. There is a reason they are so popular because they are REALLY REALLY well done."
