76561198044195889,Recommended,266510,29575880,Posted: 29 January,all,FelipeJoker,"Really nice game! Has surprised me in many ways.I've defeated the All the bosses, including the expansion ones, and I feel its enough to say that the combat in this game is not a problem, as some players may say. It does have its own way of working, though, so you should not expect the same feel you may have had with other games. I enjoyed a lot learning the way the combat flow, when to attack, how the opponents react, etc.This game is more of a risk vs reward game than anything. You get to a card. You have choices. The results may vary a little, but after you have faced it a few times, you learn how it works, and if the risk  is suitable for that session. Do you need to try to grab another weapon in the bottom of a canyon? Or are you ok with the one you have? Maybe it is a good idea to try to get that weapon to sell it, but do you have life to spare in case you fail?Also, notice that the 4-card-shuffle is possible to be followed. Yes, if you pay close attention, you may get to see the card you want being shuffled, and even if only one of the 4 cards is a success, you may follow it with your eyes and get it. (as the game progresses, this becomes harder, though!)That is another good thing to understand. I played the first 4 bosses without dying. When I had to face he las bosses, however (especially the final boss) I died over and over again, The difficulty keeps increasing! :)"
