76561198103692349,Recommended,266510,15615458,"Posted: 29 April, 2015",all,haushalterjes,"I've been intrigued by this mish mash of CCG/beat em' up since It first appeared on kickstarter, and I am so glad it turned out to be just as well conceived and addictive as I hoped it would be. First thepros:1.) Incredibly fast and fluid gameplay mechanics, simple combat but rewarding combat, excellent balance of card based mechanics and strategy elements.2.) I love the voice actor for the enigmatic dungeon master who is your constant companion throughout the game. He adds so much personality to the game and just makes you want to keep coming back just to see him alone.3.) the entire experience from the univerally woodcut artwork on the cards to the beautiful fable-inspired 3d graphics are all very beautiful and just ooze a sense of fantasy inspiration.4.) absolutely tons of cards to unlock and collect5.) addiction, seriously I bought this game on 4/29 and i've put in about 3-4 hours that day alone! I can't stop playing it.Cons:1.) the balance can be slightly unforgiving at times, it rewards cautious play rahter than risky behavior, as at times the downsides can be game-ending. Though this is part of the rouge-genre.2.) the ""card shuffling"" mini game is a bit of a mixed bag. One the one hand it's kind of addictive learning how to follow the cards on the other hand it adds an element of unpredictability to the game that takes some of the control out of your hands which makes certain pitfalls seem unfair. Which leads to frustration.3.) there are only 12 levels, which initially seems rather short, but there is an inclusion of an endless mode which is where the real meat of the game is at.In conclusion:HoF is definitely worth the buy. It's one of the most enjoyable games of the year thus far and has potential to be played for years if steam opens up a curated workshop for custom mods OR if the dev releases more dlc and more cards. Seriously they're on to something with this game. :) Pick it up."
