76561198047240355,Recommended,266510,17094309,"Posted: 17 July, 2015",all,blackbulldog,"The game is a 3D brawler, which uses cards to present opponents, loot, gear and the random encounters you'll meet.  It's a very good first game by an indie developer and I'd love to see more stuff by this team.  It's obvious that this game was made with tender loving care.Pros:The game has a wonderful aesthetic and the music and atmosphere are fantastic.   The presentation is absoultely the best thing about the game.  The voice naration and card dealing are first rate.  The game has absoultely wonderful graphics too.Cons:The brawling animations are functional, but need work.  It feels like the game isn't as responsive as it should be, and at times the small amount of input lag can cause damage or death to your character.  It's difficult to pull off 3D brawling with a counter system and I personally feel like the game would've been better if it was a 2D brawler.The camera can also be a source of frustration at times.  When your character moves farther away, the camera doesn't show the near end of the level and it's possible to not see incoming attacks.The game starts off very easy but difficulty ramps up a bit too fast for my taste.  The first few levels are very easy and by middle of the game I was struggling to reveal all the encounters and live.   By the time I hit the last couple of levels I felt like all I wanted was to just get through with as few encounters as possible, which imho is not how the game should be played,  I actually had to lower the difficulty from hard to normal for the last 3 levels because I could not finish it on hard."
