76561198037101281,Recommended,266510,13948241,"Posted: 11 January, 2015",all,lord wolfhunt,"This game is difficult to catagorize. When you start a game, it is like a DND setting. You are given a pathway of cards. Step on a card and observe it's effects. Some give you options to choose an action. Some don't. Some cards test your luck and give you rewards or punishments in turn. Sometimes, the cards force you to fight a band of monsters.Combat is where things get interesting. It is a system similar to that of Batman: Archam Asylum, but takes more skil to master. I say this because there is a bit of a difficulty spike towards the end, fair warning. Different equipment give you different benefits and your remaining health carries over between the encounter, and the pathway board, though it is all reset at the start of every run.In terms of playing, there is plenty of planing involved in going on the adventure. There is also a lot of skill involved in the combat system, but there is plenty of luck in the cards to keep things interesting with every time you play. The dungeons are procedurally generated, so every run is different, allowing for changes of strategy.There is a lot to like in this game. I do recomend it."
