76561197981201009,Not Recommended,266510,21647486,"Posted: 5 March, 2016",all,Haldar The Tall,"Sorry that this can't be recommended. I like the game concept, and there are many nice things about this game, as you can see from other reviews, and I agree with most of those reviews as to gameplay and the high production values. The killer problem, for me, is that the game is stuck in 600x400. I have tried everything I can think of, and have read all support pages, the developer's FAQ page, and in addition every Steam and Google page I can find containing the words ""Hand of Fate"" and ""resolution."" There have been lots of issues with this by other players, and also with windowing, wrong monitors displaying, and so on. Other people have complained about being stuck in resolutions HIGHER than 600x400 (wish that was my problem). None of the fixes work, at least for me. The steam launch option to select resolution does not help, in that the only selection available in the resulting launch menu is 600x400. This is true no matter what my computer's screen resolution is set to prior to launch - I have tried many different ones. Starting and switching out of windowed mode still only allows 600x400.The 600x400 resolution makes it very hard, and at times impossible, to read the text on the cards. Plus, it just looks bad.I should add that the very first time that the game played, it tried to display in higher resolution, but the graphics were too wide for the monitor at the higher resolution and the sides were cut off. I opened the in-game resolution settings, and as I was selecting alternative settings, the setting went to 600x400, and no other options since then will appear. I have deleted and downloaded the game and its local content again, to no avail. I can't delete or clear any save files or profiles, since they can not be found in the locations documented by the developers, maybe because I am running Windows 10, or maybe because there has been a recent patch, or maybe because they are now in Steam's cloud. Who knows.I do understand that for most people, the resolution is not stuck.I get the sense that the developers really cared about this game, and really tried hard, but I think they lacked the technical expertise necessary to make the game function well across so many different computer set-ups. I know this is a common problem. I'm glad I bought this on sale, because I lost only $8 instead of $25."
