,Recommended,266510,16672992,"Posted: 24 June, 2015",all,Dextron,"This is a very unique game and very well executed as well, I highly recommend it.The unusual mixture of genres leads to incredible mechanical complexity and the games employs said mechanics in a way that truly makes you feel invested, makes you care about knowing the game, to the point where knowing the cards, particularly the bosses, is key to a great advantage.As a consequence of this, you might want to turn difficulty to easy (this is done in the deck builder, counterintuitively) if you plan on playing the whole game in over a week. If you, like me, find yourself firmly grabbed by the desire to explore the game, the immense variety of cards and their associated stories will give you an abundance to explore, expect however to have to read the majority of information.The combat is carefully tutorialized and some of the weapons and artefacts feel amazing to use*, but the deck building aspect of the game requires a lot of cunning to truly get the hang of, recommended decks leave quite a bit to be desired, yet are enthusiastically pushed on the player.*I played with an XBOX One controller and it worked flawlessly, would recommend using it.The length is satisfying and there are modifiers and additional (so far) free content for good replay ability.The story, lore, and the narrator truly are the crowning jewels of this game (no spoilers ahead).You know very little about where or who you are, or about what's happening...but throughout the game you get clues, delivered by the dealer, whose comments (delivered by excellent voice acting) left me interested in the world of this game of cards like I never thought possible!Excellent writing overall.Get this game. Play this game, listen to this game, read what it has to be read.It is a unique experience that everyone can enjoy, but that will speak personally to you if you share my great love of games."
