,Recommended,266510,15812912,"Posted: 13 May, 2015",all,WHAM,"A card game in which you build decks of equipment and encounters, playing against a smart-mouthed dealer who guides you from event to event, encouter to encounter, and taunts you every step of the way, goading you on until he either gloats at your failure or grumbles at your success.That sounded pretty darn good to me, so I got Hand of Fate and played it. And I wasn't disappointed.Hand of Fate is a fairly simple game, combining a very Batman Arkham-esque combat system with an overworld card game full of decisions and chances to both succeed and fail. The random nature of the game can put some players off, though, as in the later levels you can play a near -perfect game and still fail miserably due to poor luck. Choosing your deck well can help, but it will only get you so far when the game starts doling out the ""-15 max health"" -cards.The game is occasionally a bit crude in it's visuals and animation, the dealer's card handling puts me off every time, but everything still manages to look functional and clear, easy to read and enjoyable once you get into it, and is brought together beautifully by the voice of the dealer.Hand of Fate is an enjoyable experience and well worth it's price tag. I recommend it wholeheartedly.Playtime: 10+ hours (single near-complete playthrough)Ratings (1-10)Visual: 8Audio: 8Story: 9Gameplay: 9Overall: 9"
