,Recommended,266510,18085168,"Posted: 18 September, 2015",all,ProgenitorX,"Excellent game! You traverse a dungeon whose rooms are face down cards. Each card has an event or encounter that can lead to combat, treasure, fortunes, or misfortunes. You unlock more cards as you complete events, most of them being a chain (ex. Complete the Ritual event, unlock the Lich boss fight event, complete that and unlock the Druids event storyline). There is luck involved but a lot of it is also in your hands (Do you try to sneak past an enemy or face it in hopes of good loot? Do you really want to get involved in a blood auction?).There are tons of items that make combat interesting. I'll agree the animations can be a bit clunky at times when compared to something like the Batman games (it uses the basic combat mechanics as those), but it is not as bad as most reviewers will have you believe. Combat gets pretty difficult and intense in the later half of the game, and I pretty much just beat the final boss of the game because I had bought/found just the right items to keep me alive.I would highly recommend this game to anyone who's a fan of roguelikes or just adventure games. The narrative is well written and the stories, even though they are just text through cards, are interesting and make you want to see them through. Trying to get some of the achievements can also be fun.The Wildcards DLC adds more variety to the roguelike elements by giving you Fates (classes essentially) that have a buff and a debuff on your character. It also adds Easy and Hard mode. I didn't use any Fates during my initial run, so I can't say much about the DLC, but I don't think it's worth the full price."
