,Recommended,266510,14943385,"Posted: 17 March, 2015",all,Zander,"I decided to splurge and get this game before it went on sale, and it was totally worth it. Great and very challenging game. It's a very creative combination of roguelike, deckbuilding, and hack and slash. Solid gameplay overall.My main complaint for this game is the lack of replay value. After you have beaten the game, You will have almost all of the cards, and won't want to reset the game. You can do endless mode to its full potential after the story mode, but endless mode takes out all of the deckbuilding. It would have been great to somehow include deckbuilding in endless mode.Besides that, The story was incredibly fun to play and the token system for getting new cards was very cool. I liked the little mini-game of ""following"" the chance cards when they were shuffled. The combat was surprisingly very enjoyable. The dealer had a very fitting, snarky personality. There were no glaring problems with the game save for the ending, which seemed a bit unfinished.Overall, amazing game. Highly recommend. 9/10"
76561197975902233,Recommended,266510,14682913,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,King,"I was going to pass this game by as yet another boring card game until I looked at the screenshots and saw what looked like an RPG element. This seemed interesting so I bought it, and am quite glad that I did. Not only does it have a card game element, but also a board game element (like ""Monopoly!"") and a RPG element. This makes it quite unique and better yet, all of these elements intermesh nicely. On top of that the game is executed superbly, which is a testement to the game designers skills. The difficulty of the game increases at a frustrating, yet manageable rate. At first it seemed that the lack of a saving the game and keeping your items was a weakness, but in the end it was a strength. It made it mandatory to use different item combinations early in each new game to survive, which often produced unexpected results leading to an advancement path that I likely would not have otherwise tried. The crucial dealer character is well done and appropriately sarcastic and arrogant at times, and other  times cajoling and supportive of your efforts. That made his inevitable defeat most satisfying.  The final battle I thought was well done, whereas in other games it is a disappointing afterthought. I am still playing the game to round up the last few tokens I havent gotten and intend to play the endless mode from time to time for amusement. Be warned this game is highly addictive and you can expect to lose a whole weekend or week before you are satisfied. The only question I have is how long do I have to wait for the sequel?"
