,Recommended,266510,16768817,"Posted: 28 June, 2015",all,ggab,"Really interesting blend of mechanics that has some implementation problems (I go into it in the spoiler senction). The roguelike aspect, the deckbuilding aspect, the choose-your-own-aventure aspect and the third person brawler aspect all blend toghether really well. Yes, the game is not the best one in any of these mechanics, so if you don't like the whole package you'll find a better experience elsewhere. Maybe Batman, Binding of Isaac or The Yawgh.Performance wise it's not a heavy game but, since all the cards are individual models and are manipulated several times by the Dealer, it might choke on a few points on lower end computers.This would be alongside my favorites if it wasn't for some (really bad) late game decisions.SPOILER SECTION....The final boss is a complete joke. I problably spent half of my gameplay hours on him. It ramps up the dificulty, but not in a good way. The dificulty of the final level is that it slowly chips away at your health and abilities with a curse at every stage and the inability to aquire blessings (this can be changed if you're lucky and has the proper cards).The final boss is a gauntlet of all previous bosses, separetad by enemy type. This woul be easy if the three plague bosses wheren't so OP. The king and the jack have a small window of vulnerabillity and they usually stunlock you and take a lot of health, the king specially. The problem is not defeat them, but to do so without loosing much health.Between matches with the previous bosses the Dealer unleashes some magical attacks and there's a QTE. The last one is my main death reason because it's really hard to dodge all of them. It can easilly hit you for 40+ hp and with your health already chipped away by all the previous bosses... you got the picture.The cheap way around it is to kill the game before dying. The game saves just before the fight for crash prevention purposes. That way you don't have to pass through all the maze again. Hell, if you're feeling particularly cheap you can do that every time  something bad happens to you so you arrive at the last battle in better condition."
