,Recommended,266510,14542758,"Posted: 19 February, 2015",all,Enzocreed,"This game is fantastic, a nice mix of deckbuilding, choose your own adventure and fable/arkham style combat, the narration of the game is comes from the card dealer, a kind of forture teller character who you could refer to as your dungeon master for the game.Other reviewers have complained about the combat style, btu having played the game since it first came out on early access I can confidently say it feels Kinetic and viceral, while allowing the player to dodge and counter easily.  While the game might start out a bit easy the difficulty curve does start to ramp up as the game progresses.The Sound design is very nice, the music in particular lends a nice fantasy feel, and does a good job of lifting the player up and making them feel good about their victories, and as previously mentioned the narrator keeps the player engaged at all times, even coming out with different remarks based on your actions that keep you wanting to push on.The graphics are simple but look very pretty when turned up all the way, some of the small arenas may get repetitive at the start but once again the game does a good job of pacing itself, while adding new traps and environmental risks into the mix as play progresses.  The actual graphics style gives me flashbacks to the slightly cartoony aesthetic of the fable series.I have yet to finish the game, but I am over halfway through it and so far it has kept me well satisfied and the developer has already said they plan to add more content based on community suggestions and feedback.My only bit of dissapointment would be that there is no option for changing the look of the character, even a couple of presets would be nice, hopefully now that the game is out this may be added at a future date.In conclusion, Hand of Fate is fantastic, and if you have any quarms about paying the full near £20 for this game (which I think is a very reasonable price for a game of this quality and length) then stick it on your watch list and grab it as soon as it does, I love it!"
