76561197963703216,Recommended,266510,14677655,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,Galm Whitemane,"An absolutely charming game. Roguelike real-time combat meets card game with an engaging campaign which may seem very easy at first, but soon enough ramps up the difficulty. You craft both your own deck and the dealer's and progress your collection through your interactions with the cards during play, unlocking new cards which are often thematic ""sequels"" of the card before it.New conditions apply each round and the dealer adds in fixed cards for each campaign step, making you re-think your decks and what you need. You know you'll get a curse every level? Add a ring to your deck that raises your damage for each curse you're suffering - an example of many.The dealer is your mysterious opponent, always with a quip ready for your struggles and he has you continually second-guess the nature of the game and he himself with droplets of exposition.While I haven't tried Endless mode, I likely will, just to unlock every last card. Campaign alone is certainly worth the price."
