76561197983672075,Recommended,266510,14818358,"Posted: 9 March, 2015",all,DaetherX,"Wow... Just... Enjoyable...Like a ""Choose Your Own Adventure"" book via cards being laid out mostly from a deck that you put together from ones you've earned. One deck for equipment, another for encounters that are placed for your token to move along, and as you do flip over to discover and challenge them, then in each boss/scenario selection the mysterious dealer (who has many well spoken lines of dialogue) adds a few of his own ""to keep things interesting"".Each scenario ends when you die or defeat the boss you selected.There is 3D brawler style combat that works well. Nothing to say about combat system except that it is competent. It gives moments of action to savor (or dread) in between the interesting artwork and event cards. It's simple, but works well, and is varied enough depending on the enemy mix and your current equipment.There is an ""Endless"" mode as well that is unlocked after defeating 2 or 3 bossess which gives this game a high replayability when combined with the decks building apect since one run with certain card selection will go differently than with another. Even with the same card selection, though, they will be different as equipment cards are randomly given via winning events or battles which are randomly selected and laid out for you to traverse."
