,Recommended,266510,14571739,"Posted: 20 February, 2015",all,Xephael,"I've only played the game for a little over an hour, and I already know I can highly recommend it. The game has a very simple concept; you create two decks of cards, one of equipment and one of encounters. As you play you unlock new cards that you can add to your decks, but there's a catch. You wont know what a specific card does until you encounter it in the game for the first time. The dealer also has his own deck that will also be enhanced as you collect more cards for yours.Something that some will consider a downside is that the combat is fairly simplistic. You can have some abilities in the form of artifact cards or special equipment, but for the most part combat consists of basic attacking and countering with a shield. The combat still manages to be intense and extremely satisfying when you win despite, and perhaps due to, it's simplicity.Overall I would recommend the game wholeheartedly to anyone looking for a fun and satisfying adventure.9.75/10"
,Recommended,266510,14572554,"Posted: 21 February, 2015",all,Darthus,"This game is hard to describe, but that's because the structure is so fresh and original. The experience is like playing one of those great fantasy board story board games like Hero's Quest. I think when most people hear it's a card or deckbuilding game they think Magic or Hearthstone, but it's much more akin to a tile based RPG where you move around a board having little narrated story encounters, which sometimes drop down into 3D action combat. It just happens to be that the ""board"" you're playing on, the monsters you encounter and the gear you gain, are drawn from decks of cards that you can configure (or let the game choose) beforehand. Really what makes this game sing though is the presentation. The wonderful moody thematic voice-over of the wizard you are playing against, where he comments on every card and action thematically, the awesome art of the cards, the general graphical polish makes it feel like playing a real fantasy RPG card game come to life. The combat is... workman-like and servicable, but it's honestly only a portion of the overall experience. Highly recommended and I hope that DLC comes to expand it as this is an amazing structure for a game."
