76561198030978104,Recommended,266510,14601285,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,Tylermcd93,"First and foremost I absolutely love this game for so many reasons. I can sometimes steer clear of card game video games because they can be very lackluster for me. So at first I was hesitant in getting this game. However that was until I watched a gameplay video on Youtube of this game. I then realized how wrong I was and what I was missing out. I was missing out on such a unique take on card games. This has little to do with strategy like most card games but is more about choosing your own adventure. Each game in the story mode takes about 20 or so minutes to go through so it's very easy to manage your time with this game. I've seen people complain about RNG in this game however it's honestly not that big of a deal. RNG only happens with card draws, room layouts, and success chances on certain encounters. The combat is a feature that I really like about this game. The combat is hack and slash, dodge and counter type of combat which I think is really smart to put into a card game because it deter from the possible monotony that a lot of card games have. Every game is different and it has high replayability because of it and Endless Mode which is where you can try and go in a game for as long as you can until you die. A very good gem of a game that I regret not partaking in the Early Access stage of it's life. 10/10 will always play again."
