76561197989597242,Recommended,266510,23692987,"Posted: 21 June, 2016",all,bloodspot88,"This game is one-of-a-kind. Although I have spent tens of hours playing it, I have yet to beat it.The point of the game is to advance throughout a deck of cards, moving a token on the card and revealing challanges or events along the way. As you build your deck with better equipment and event cards, you have a higher penalty for higher rewards, making the game swing either way depending on how you improve while you play.The combat system is simple and works as a junior version of the batman combat system. It isn't really where the game shines, though it offers many difficulties on its own when multiple enemy types are fought in one combat session.The graphics for the dealer and cards are nice, but the combat graphics look plastered on. If you're anal retentive about everything in your game being beatufiul, move on.My overall point is this: If you like collecting things, you'll love this game. You have to replay scenarios over and over unless you're skilled at following the cards, and when you finally get the beast gear from all the tokens in the game you can beat it relatively easily. But if you don't like attempting the same checks over and over and don't want to spend higher than 10 hours into a game like this, you probably won't beat it as I find the best tokens in the game are extremely hard to obtain."
