,Recommended,266510,24022297,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,Vexitus,"Hand of Fate is a card adventure/RPG game, in the beginning you choose a boss to fight through each tier of the game. The game is a linear, but random adventure based on the deck you build. As you move along the path of cards you will face challenges that will be random much like a tabletop game's dice you will select a card and there will be consequences for winning and losing such as winning gold/items, losing food, losing health, fighting enemies, earning blessings/curses, etc. As the game progresses your character will gain loot which will benefit him in combat. The combat feels like the Batman series games where you strike and coutner when the chances arises. When you reach the end of the path you fight the boss who has special abilities and sometimes cannot be blocked. Hand of Fate is very fun and random which can seriously make you think back on your previous choices. It is not without its problems though, the combat is relatively easy, there is really one character you play as, and you are really only limited to melee combat (though it makes since because of the size of the arenas. Still Hand of Fate's goods outweighs the bads and it does create some replability just for the fact that it is random and each time you move forward by defeating bosses you earn new cards to experience and play in previous levels. I will give this game a positive review and hopefully there will be some DLC in the future."
