76561197988566726,Recommended,266510,21955643,"Posted: 20 March, 2016",all,Grim Jester,"I'm not sure where to begin, so I'll list the three ways in which this game shines:1) Your companion is called The Dealer. His voice acting, and writing is excellent. Sometimes he insults you, sometimes he helps you, and sometimes he says something profound.2) The combat seems to be inspired by Arkham Asylum. You can attack, counter, and dodge. More than that, the order in which you take out opponents is important. Beyond that, the gear that you equip can make you more or less effective against certain opponents.3) Lastly, this is a deck builder game. For those of you who don't know, a deck builder is a game where adding and subtracting cards from your deck makes you more, or less effective in play.This game can be very hard on the normal setting for three reasons:1) Like FTL, and Rogue Legacy, you must have a certain amount of luck to get the tools that you need to beat the game. When you've played enough to understand this, don't be afraid to forfeit a game early, and restart. Luck is a necessary ingredient for success.2) If you don't understand how a deck builder works, you won't be able to stack the deck in your favor. This is an important part of the game. The basics are simple, you add good cards, and remove bad cards.3) Some creatures must be killed first before you can kill any other creatures. If you are constantly failing in a particular combat scenario, look up some hints online, and it will be made clear.One more note, a large portion of the game uses a variant of 3 Card Monte, a popular con game. It is sometimes, but not always, possible to track the card that you want, so don't assume that it's totally random."
