76561197983833091,Recommended,266510,25462290,"Posted: 11 September, 2016",all,ozzydto,"Great game that relies on the choices you make as well as fighting skill and some luck.You have a deck of encounter cards, these get arranged into dungeon levels which your hero steps through. The challenge being that you have to balnce your health, gold and food as you go so that you survive in the long term. You start off with a fixed deck of cards, but each encounter is usually part of a chain that you progress through, so the one you just completed is discarded and then in your next game the new card will be added. This is how new loot and gear are also added to the mix.Not all encounters are combat related, with text describing a situation, then offering some choices to make. There are some that present you with a sort-of luck based success/fail (its one of those follow the card as they are shuffled mini games) which can be frustrating, but its a mechanic that works.Some may find the combat either too simple, or get annoyed by controls, camera,etc, but I think it works well since its not the sole focus of the game and so doesn't drag on too much.Its a great game, worth picking up if you see it on sale."
