76561198008031054,Recommended,266510,14790834,"Posted: 8 March, 2015",all,KitchenGun,"In most RPGs, card games are a staple mini-game where you can use the cards collected in random encounters. Sometimes, these games are fun like tetra master in FFIX, but most of the time they are just a distraction and play-time-extenders.With this game, however, it's the other way around. Collecting and playing cards is the main part, while the hack-and-slay-style encounters and bosses are fun, but do not compare to the excitement of unlocking new cards and the adventures and mysteries they hold.It all comes together when a round ends: Regardless of the outcome, each token acquired in the game unlocks new cards that have effects that are yet unknown - you have to uncover their meaning in-game. Then, the dealer invites you to play another game. He let's all your cards hover in a cloud above the table and you just have to click to start another round to get to know your new acquisitions...Highly recommended, especially for players that cannot resist an innovative rogue-like or card-game with many collectibles."
