,Recommended,266510,14652304,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,ThaProfessor,"This game is incredibly fun. There is enough RNG that humbles even the most experienced of gamers. If you're comfortable with the fighting style of the Arkham series (flowing combos and countering) then the combat shouldn't be too difficult. The game really thrives in its ability to conjure a new experience every time you enter the gauntlet -- Nothing like fighting off 16 enemies with a rusty axe and hoping for the best.PROS: Well designed, voice acting is excellent, graphics are quite nice and the uniqueness of each level of the dungeon keeps me coming to play this game. You unlock more cards as you defeat their predecessors to extend the replayability.CONS: Entering a prone attack can be frustrating, simply because you stand there like a doofus and swing your weapon which in turn inspires enemies to want to start their attack patterns earlier...probably because they got each other's backs. What generally happens is that you enter a prone attack, get 1 or 2 swings in, and just roll away...never really finishing the attack."
