,Recommended,266510,16904235,"Posted: 5 July, 2015",all,MidnightSnacks,"Build a deck with helpful items and events. A dealer adds some of his own including a boss which has some overall rule like ""lose gold every turn"" or ""shop prices are low but you get cursed for buying anything"". Start at point A and hop onto face-down cards to flip them and try to find point B. Most will be random events with a x-card Monte minigame to determine whether it resolves positively or negatively. You get a token the first time you complete a challenge correctly, which typically but not always is by getting the positive result. Manage food, gold, and health, win equipment and blessings to strengthen your character for battle challenges (typical negative event result plus every round ends with an boss fight, at least), and avoid curses which are basically just negative blessings. If you beat the boss your collected tokens turn into new cards. If you die at any point you lose your tokens from that round and start over.Each round of the game is pretty short, and at least working through the story the first time there's a solid sense of progression from the deck building. I also really like the voice acting for the Dealer, he's a pretty charming character. On the base difficulty at least, if you're familiar with how Arkham combat works then you really can't lose a combat event. There's some challenge modes I can't vouch for yet."
