,Recommended,266510,26578360,"Posted: 13 November, 2016",all,ThePCGamer101,"DISCLAIMER: This is a first impressions review, and NOT a full review, if you want a full review, then please read better reviews then mineHand of Fate is a card game developed and published by Defiant Development. As mentioned previously, Hand of Fate is a card game brought to life with Batman Arkham style combat and deckbuilding to customize your events and equipment pool. It also offers an endless mode where you have to survive for as long as possible with every card you've ever gotten mixed in the freyThe game offers responsive combat and a huge variety of equipment, monsters and events. The card artwork on each card given to you is really well made and fantastic music by Jeff van DyckThe dealers narration is well-produced. There is a fairly lengthy story mode and a more rogue-like endless mode and the game offers a very stylized graphics that looks great. The game dynamically get's more difficult as your opponent's own deck improves alongside yours with more enemies and negative outcomes the more you progressHowever, bosses are fairly week when you first encounter them so it feels sligthly anti-climactic and several of the weapons are straight up just upgrades over others meaning that meta decks get very similar. Every weapon is one handed so despite what you're using combat is always the same mostly, also the animations during combat are pretty weakI really did enjoy Hand of Fate, I highly recommend this game for anyone looking for a good rogue-like and also for people unfamiliar with the genre and want a more simplistic game with easy to learn but hard to master combat and with all the little issues the game has, I hope these will be ironed out in Hand of Fate 2!RECOMMENDED :)"
