,Recommended,266510,28704288,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,Ike,"This game is everything I wanted and more. It's brilliantly made and has a very fun and easy to enjoy battle system. I first saw this video in a paid promotion and I was pre-emptively gagging, expecting some cash grab. I watched on and what I saw looked amazing. It's a game of chance, requires some strategic thinking and is loads of fun. Sometimes you feel awesome and super lucky, while other times you just feel wrecked, but usually you can play well enough to mitigate the bad outcomes. I wholeheartedly recommend this if you've ever enjoyed a roguelike game before, or a card game. It's the best of both, with tons of progression.Pros: Good lore, fun gameplay, interesting character designs, interesting encounters, a surpising amount of progression and a ton of depth. Lots of replayability, extremely addicting. Once you begin collecting tokens, you just can't stop.Cons: There's barely any music, but what little there is, it's pretty good. There is a lot of luck elements, but it's a card game all about fate and chance, so this is barely even a drawback. Also, this game is extremely addictive. Hard not to play over and over and say to yourself ""Alright, last game- Ah crap it's 3 am? Whatever, just one more.""Would buy again, especially while it's on sale. DEFINITELY get this if you're considering it, you won't regret it one bit! (Unless you hate getting unlucky, then maybe. But pro tip, you can track cards with your eyes so it's never that luck based!)"
