,Recommended,266510,31101921,Posted: 12 April,all,Cross Kamui,"Game has two modes:Story mode (you fight your way through a set o bosses)Endless mode (you fight and die for no reason)PRO:- Tarot card concept- Nice and unique illustrations- Well thought world and detailed story- Animated board game style- Dealer has a lot of dialogues, which are unique and well voice-acted- Blessing and curse cards shape your fate and contribute to a dynamic difficulty- The game is coherent, there are several good ideas, which contribute to deliver a great experience- Your decisions may have a great impact on your futureCONTRA:- There may be some unbalanced situations- Reading the encounter text and listening to the dealer in the same time can be disturbing after a while (dealer should shut up sometimes :D) - Settings, voice volume can be turned down thankfully- After replaying certain levels, the player has to listen to the lengthy comments of the dealer (usually after chalice/scepter/disk/dagger is unlocked)- Achievements will require you some HEAVY grinding which may kill the adventurous spiritThis game is a rare gem. You should get it, and play it!Be prepared that after mid-game your hand will not be held anymore - even if you have the impression of it - and you may be beaten really hard.Furthermore, there are some issues (they don't happen often, which is good):High Success: -50% Max health on Level 21 Endless, Sunken TreasureHigh Success: -15 Max health Secret Society (still on Endless)Devs, if you have the time and some spare resources, please fix these issues. This game may become a legend and one where players will be returning even after long years!"
